# Git workflow

Hard rules for branches, PRs, and merges.

## Branches

- Never commit directly to `main` or `master`.
- Feature work: `feat/<short-name>`
- Bug fixes: `fix/<short-name>`
- Documentation: `docs/<short-name>`

## Pull requests

- Open every change as a PR into `main`.
- All CI checks must pass before merge.
- Squash or merge commit per repo default.
- One logical change per PR when possible.

## Force push

- Never force-push `main` or `master`.
- Force-push feature branches only when explicitly requested.

## Do not commit

- `.env` and other secrets or credential files
- `.pnpm-store/` (local pnpm cache)
- `docs/superpowers/` agent scratch notes
